MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
A dog and pony show will be filmed on the Los Angeles set of MCA-TV's new 
"Lassie" series when the miniature horse Ragtime joins Lassie as a guest star. 
Ragtime's owner, Patty Fairchild, recently won an appellate courtroom decision 
allowing the miniature horse to remain living indoors in Fairchild's Thousand 
Oaks home. The syndicated "Lassie," starring Dee Wallace Stone and Christopher 
Stone, is scheduled to debut on KHJ-TV Channel 9 in September. A firm air date 
has not been set. Daniel Cerone and Claudia Puig 
